      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "In Judge Huneke's department of\nthe superior court the suit of the\nGreat Northern railway to condemn\na portion of the grounds belonging\nTO the Whittier school is on trial.\nThe school is located in the West\nGrove district and the ground is\nneeded for the connecting line be-\ntween the s., p. & S. and the Great\nNorthern. The railroad wants to\npay for only the amount of ground\nactually taken, while the school\nboard claims that the whole of the\nground and the building is rendered\nuseless for school purposes."
    }
